## 1. Purpose
This document defines [COMPANY]'s internal audit program for the ISMS: its scope, independence requirements, schedule, methodology, reporting, and follow-up. Internal audit provides independent assurance that controls are designed and operating effectively, that the ISMS conforms to its own requirements and to HITRUST/HIPAA, and it readies the organization for external assessment.

## 2. Scope
Covers internal auditing of all controls and processes within the ISMS scope (`isms-scope-statement.md.template`), across in-scope [AWS], [Snowflake], and [GitHub] systems, supporting SaaS, and administrative processes. Internal audit is distinct from, and complementary to, external HITRUST/SOC 2 assessments.

## 3. Policy
1. The ISMS **shall** be internally audited at planned intervals such that every applicable control is audited at least once per [assessment cycle / annually], with a risk-based frequency that audits PHI-handling and high-risk areas more often.
2. Auditors **shall** be independent of the activities they audit; an auditor **shall not** audit their own work.
3. Audits **shall** follow a documented methodology and produce evidence-based findings rated by severity.
4. Findings **shall** be reported to the relevant control owners and to [top management], and entered into the corrective-action / POA&M register (`corrective-action-poam.md.template`).
5. Corrective actions **shall** be tracked to closure and verified by follow-up.
6. The audit plan and results **shall** be inputs to management review (`management-review.md.template`).

## 4. Roles & Responsibilities
| Role | Responsibility |
|---|---|
| [Compliance / Audit Lead] | Owns the program; maintains the audit plan; assigns independent auditors. |
| Auditors (internal or contracted) | Conduct audits objectively; document evidence and findings. |
| Control / Process Owners | Provide evidence; own and remediate findings. |
| [Security Officer / CISO] | Receives results; ensures remediation resourcing. |
| [CEO / Board] | Receives summary assurance; supports independence. |

See `roles-and-responsibilities.md.template` for full role definitions.

## 5. Independence & Objectivity
Auditors **shall** be free from conflicts of interest with the area under review. Where the organization is too small for full separation, independence is achieved by [peer review of an area the auditor does not operate], [rotating reviewers], or [engaging an external assessor]. Auditor independence for each engagement is documented in the audit plan.

## 6. Audit Schedule
An annual, risk-based audit plan **shall** be maintained and approved, covering which controls/domains are audited, when, and by whom.

| Area / Domain | Risk | Frequency | Auditor (independent of area) |
|---|---|---|---|
| Access control & privileged access | High | [Semi-annual] | [Assigned] |
| PHI handling & data protection | High | [Semi-annual] | [Assigned] |
| Vulnerability & patch management | High | [Annual] | [Assigned] |
| Change management & CI/CD ([GitHub]) | Medium | [Annual] | [Assigned] |
| Logging & monitoring ([AWS]/[Snowflake]) | Medium | [Annual] | [Assigned] |
| Vendor / BAA management | Medium | [Annual] | [Assigned] |
| Governance, policies, training | Low | [Annual] | [Assigned] |

## 7. Methodology
1. **Plan:** define objectives, scope, criteria (policy + HITRUST/HIPAA), and sample.
2. **Conduct:** examine evidence, interview owners, test control operation against criteria.
3. **Evaluate & rate:** classify each finding (e.g., Critical / High / Medium / Low / Observation) by risk and impact.
4. **Document:** record evidence, findings, and conclusions in an audit report.
5. **Validate:** confirm findings with control owners before finalizing.

## 8. Reporting
Each audit produces a report stating scope, criteria, findings with severity, evidence, and recommendations. Reports are issued to control owners and [top management] and summarized for the Steering Committee and management review. Audit reports are retained as ISMS records per `document-control.md.template`.

## 9. Follow-up & Closure
Each finding is logged in the POA&M register with an owner, remediation plan, and due date. The [Compliance / Audit Lead] tracks remediation and performs follow-up verification, confirming the corrective action effectively addressed the root cause before closing the finding.

## 10. Exceptions
Deviations from the audit plan (e.g., a deferred audit) require documented rationale per `exceptions-and-waivers.md.template`, approved by the [Security Officer], time-bound, and recorded.

## 11. Compliance, Monitoring & Enforcement
The audit program's execution is itself evidenced and reviewed at management review and during external assessment. Obstruction of an audit or failure to remediate findings is an ISMS deficiency; conduct issues are handled per `../people/hr-security-policy.md.template`.

